messages.text: Which is bigger: 9.11 or 9.9? Explain your reasoning.

9.9 is bigger than 9.11.

Reasoning by place-value:

1. Write both with the same number of decimal places:
   • 9.9   = 9.90  
   • 9.11  = 9.11  

2. Compare digit by digit from left to right:
   – The “9” before the decimal point is the same in both.  
   – In the tenths place:  
     • 9.90 has a 9 in the tenths place  
     • 9.11 has a 1 in the tenths place  
     Since 9 > 1, 9.90 (i.e. 9.9) is larger than 9.11.

Alternatively, multiply both by 100 to eliminate the decimal:

   • 9.11 × 100 = 911  
   • 9.9 × 100  = 990  

And 990 > 911, so 9.9 > 9.11.
